content:
Get up and running with Service Cloud Voice. Before you start, review the Voice prerequisites, limitations, and planning resources.

Service Cloud Voice comes in several flavors: 
- Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect leverages the power of Amazon Connect telephony to give agents, supervisors, and customers a seamless service experience.
- Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect lets you integrate your Amazon Connect instance with Service Cloud Voice.
- Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony lets you create a Service Cloud Voice contact center that uses a telephony provider of your choice.

Setup Prerequisites:
- Complete these prerequisites before setting up Service Cloud Voice.

Set Up Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect: 
- Review the prerequisites, limitations, and planning resources for Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect.
Set Up Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony: 
- Review the prerequisites, limitations, and planning resources for Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony.
Set Up Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect: 
- Review the Voice prerequisites, limitations, and planning resources before integrating your Amazon Connect instance with Service Cloud Voice.

Configure Your Contact Center:
- Set up a phone channel and add agents to the contact center.
- Set up workspaces for agents and supervisors in the contact center.

Best Practices for Service Cloud Voice:
- Ensure your contact center runs optimally by reviewing these best practices.
title: Setting Up Service Cloud Voice
